nstein has produced a meticulous new edition which includes both the first version, Anecdotes of Sir W. Scott and the later version. She provides a wealth of new information about these lively, readable, idiosyncratic, and disconcerting texts."  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 4aLiterary Studies. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh1 aMack, Douglas S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRubenstein, J H, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aRubenstein, Jill, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aShepherd, Ettrick, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEdinburgh University Press Archive eBook-Package Pre-2000z978311078047540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978074869864640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780748698646423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780748698646/original  a978-3-11-078047-5  Edinburgh University Press Archive eBook-Package Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK